# Prerequisites


This manual detailed an installation solution of the chemotion_ELN system. We will used Microsoft Subsystem for Linux.The instructions in this manual have been tested on Windows 10. Depending on your base operating system, the following packages must be installed:


### Dependencies

• Install ubuntu (20.04.2) on windows 
• Install Desktop Docker (https://hub.docker.com/editions/community/docker-ce-desktop-windows/)



## Tools recommended for development

Visual Studio Code 
• Install Visual studio code with linters set up (es and ruby-rubocop):
  https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=rebornix.Ruby && https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=dbaeumer.vscode-eslint

visual studio code with Version control 
https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/editor/github
https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/editor/versioncontrol

when Vim 
check https://github.com/dense-analysis/ale


# Setup

Set docker desktop setting (Docker Desktop Stable 2.3.0.2 https://docs.docker.com/docker-for-windows/wsl/)
•	From the Docker menu, select Settings > General.
•	Select the Use WSL 2 based engine check box.
•	Enable integration with additional distro: ubuntu
•	Select Ubuntu distributions you must enable the Docker-WSL integration on.


The setup continues with the following steps:


      
Set path on PowerShell (Windows)

```
cd c:\chemotion\...

```

Set path on terminal (Ubuntu)

```

cd /mnt/c

```
### Optional
Set a path of PostgreSQL on docker-compose.yml 
db:
- /home/chemotion/db-data:/var/lib/postgresql/data/

You can proceed to the next step by navigating the provided link.
https://www.chemotion.net/chemotionsaurus/docs/eln/DevDocker

